    <item>
      <title>LaTeX and Markdown spell check in Atom</title>
      <link>https://blog.lopezjuri.com/2015/12/29/latex-and-markdown-spell-check-in-atom/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 29 Dec 2015 23:55:08 -0300</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blog.lopezjuri.com/2015/12/29/latex-and-markdown-spell-check-in-atom/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;figure &gt;
    
        &lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.lopezjuri.com/images/atom-spellcheck.gif&#34; /&gt;
    
    
&lt;/figure&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I use Atom for everything. In the last days, I have wrote a lot of text in Markdown and LaTeX, but english is not my main language so I spend some time searching lint tools and plugins to help me out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Atoms comes with a spell-check plugin, but it does not lint every file type.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To enable Markdown and LaTeX:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;text.tex.latex, source.gfm
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;


&lt;figure &gt;
    
        &lt;img src=&#34;https://blog.lopezjuri.com/images/atom-spellcheck-settings.png&#34; /&gt;
    
    
&lt;/figure&gt;


&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;CMD+SHIFT+.&lt;/code&gt; to show the suggestions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
